# Stripe Integration Environment Variables
# 
# INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local (for local development)
# 2. Replace the placeholder values with your actual Stripe keys
# 3. DO NOT commit .env.local to git (already in .gitignore)
# 4. On Vercel/Netlify, add these same variables in the dashboard
#
# How to find your keys:
# 1. Go to https://dashboard.stripe.com/
# 2. Click "Developers" in the left sidebar
# 3. Click "API Keys" tab
#
# For STRIPE_SECRET_KEY:
# - Use the "Secret key" (starts with sk_live_ or sk_test_)
# - NEVER expose this in frontend code
#
# For STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET:
# - Go to "Webhooks" section
# - Click on your webhook endpoint
# - Copy the "Signing secret" (starts with whsec_)

# ============================================================================
# DEVELOPMENT (Test Mode) - Use test keys for development
# ============================================================================
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_YOUR_TEST_SECRET_KEY_HERE
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_YOUR_TEST_WEBHOOK_SECRET_HERE

# ============================================================================
# PRODUCTION (Live Mode) - Uncomment and use live keys for production
# ============================================================================
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_live_YOUR_LIVE_SECRET_KEY_HERE
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_YOUR_LIVE_WEBHOOK_SECRET_HERE

# ============================================================================
# SECURITY WARNINGS
# ============================================================================
# ⚠️  NEVER commit this file with real secrets
# ⚠️  NEVER expose SECRET_KEY in frontend code
# ⚠️  NEVER share these keys publicly
# ⚠️  NEVER use live keys for testing
# ⚠️  NEVER commit .env files to git
